Mastering Linux commands is a journey, not a destination. Start with the basics, practice regularly, and gradually incorporate advanced commands into your workflow.

ğŸ’¡ Key Takeaways:

â€¢ Start with basic navigation (pwd, ls, cd)

â€¢ Learn file operations before moving to advanced topics

â€¢ Use man pages and --help for detailed documentation

â€¢ Practice in a safe environment before using on production

â€¢ Create aliases for frequently used commands

â€¢ Always verify commands before using sudo

